{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "ed0a89da-2470-46d4-a837-acf0e036d99c",
    "name": "StarClinch API",
    "description": "This collection covers the core REST API endpoints for the **StarClinch** platform, which supports two distinct user roles — **Sellers** and **Customers** — along with a **Recipe** management system.\n\n### Authentication\n\nHandles account registration, login, profile retrieval, and account deletion for both Sellers and Customers. Token-based authentication is used, with tokens stored in the `seller_token` and `customer_token` environment variables for reuse across requests.\n\n- Register Seller / Register Customer\n    \n- Login Seller / Login Customer\n    \n- Get Profile (Seller)\n    \n- Delete Seller Account / Delete Customer Account\n    \n\n### Recipes\n\nSellers can create, update, and delete recipes. Both Sellers and Customers can browse and view individual recipes. Customers can also rate recipes.\n\n- Add Recipe\n    \n- Get All Recipes\n    \n- Get Single Recipe\n    \n- Update Recipe\n    \n- Delete Recipe (Seller)\n    \n- Rate Recipe\n    \n\n### Environment Variables\n\nThe collection relies on the following environment variables:\n\n- `base_url` — Base URL of the API server\n    \n- `seller_token` — Auth token for Seller requests\n    \n- `customer_token` — Auth token for Customer requests\n    \n- `recipe_id` — ID of the recipe used in single-recipe and rating operations",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "48145409",
    "_collection_link": "https://go.postman.co/collection/48145409-ed0a89da-2470-46d4-a837-acf0e036d99c?source=collection_link"
  },
